Parameters: @bin2inc [input file] [output file] [name of array]
<p>@bin2inc will convert a binary file (param 1) to a TRSE .include file (param 2) that
contains an array with the data from the binary file.
<code>
@incbin "data.bin" "data.inc" "myData"
</code>
"data.inc" will now look something like this:
</code>
var myData : array [32] of byte = ($10,$20,$30 ....);
</code>
